==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]'') smî, /smɪə/, /<tt>smI@</tt>/
*(''US'') smîr, /smɪɚ/, /<tt>smI@`</tt>/

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|smear||}}

#To spread (a substance, especially one that colours or is dirty) across a surface by rubbing.
#:''The artist smeared paint over the canvas in broad strokes.''
#To have a substance smeared on (a surface).
#:''She smeared her lips with lipstick.''

====Synonyms====
*(''spread (a substance)''): [[spread]]
*(''have a substance smeared on''): [[coat]], [[cover]], [[layer]]

